    "plan_content": "Here's the complete plan for the `ollama rename` feature. It touches **4 files** with **8 targeted insertions**, reuses all existing infrastructure, and requires no new imports anywhere.\n\n---\n\n## What gets added\n\n### `api/types.go` — new struct (after `CopyRequest`, line 765)\n```go\ntype RenameRequest struct {\n    Source      string `json:\"source\"`\n    Destination string `json:\"destination\"`\n}\n```\n\n### `api/client.go` — new method (after `Copy`, line 387)\n```go\nfunc (c *Client) Rename(ctx context.Context, req *RenameRequest) error {\n    return c.do(ctx, http.MethodPost, \"/api/rename\", req, nil)\n}\n```\n\n### `server/routes.go` — `RenameHandler` (after `CopyHandler`, line 1483)\nThe handler follows this sequence:\n1. Parse + validate **source** → 400 Bad Request if invalid\n2. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` → **404** if `os.IsNotExist`; save as `srcManifest`\n3. Parse + validate **destination** → 400 if invalid\n4. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst) == nil` → **409 Conflict** if destination exists\n5. `CopyModel(src, dst)` — copies the lightweight manifest file; blobs are shared by SHA256 digest, so no data is duplicated\n6. `srcManifest.Remove()` — deletes source manifest file\n7. `srcManifest.RemoveLayers()` — GCs orphaned blobs; since destination now references all layers, nothing gets deleted\n\nRoute registered: `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)` (after the copy route, line 1698)\n\n### `cmd/cmd.go` — CLI (3 insertion points)\n```go\n// Handler function (after CopyHandler, line 1350)\nfunc RenameHandler(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) error { ... }\n\n// Command definition (after copyCmd, line 2263)\nrenameCmd := &cobra.Command{Use: \"rename SOURCE DESTINATION\", Short: \"Rename a model\", ...}\n\n// Registration in rootCmd.AddCommand and env-docs loop\n```\n\n---\n\n## Critical design insight\n`srcManifest` is captured **before** the copy. By the time `RemoveLayers()` runs, the destination manifest already exists on disk — so `RemoveLayers()` scans all remaining manifests, sees all blobs are still referenced by the destination, and correctly deletes nothing. The rename is safe and blob-preserving.",
